# Auto Configuration ⚙️

## 📖 What is Auto Configuration?

**Auto Configuration** is one of the most powerful features of Spring Boot.

It automatically configures your Spring application based on the dependencies available in the classpath.

In simple words:

> **Spring Boot automatically sets up the required configuration so that developers don't have to write it manually.**

---

# 🎯 Why Auto Configuration?

Before Spring Boot:

❌ Configure DispatcherServlet

❌ Configure Tomcat

❌ Configure DataSource

❌ Configure Hibernate

❌ Configure Bean Definitions

❌ Write XML Configuration

With Spring Boot:

✅ Automatic Configuration

✅ Less Boilerplate Code

✅ Faster Development

✅ Production Ready Setup

---

# 🌟 How Auto Configuration Works

Spring Boot checks:

* Available Dependencies
* Existing Beans
* Configuration Properties
* Environment Variables

Then it automatically configures the application.

---

